      "thinking": {
        "text": "\nThis is a question about LTO performance comparing two specific premium LTO items (Big Shack and Dubai Chocolate Shake) across two channels (in-Shack kiosk vs third-party delivery) and filtered to the top 20 highest-volume locations.\n\nLet me break down what I need:\n1. Two specific LTO items: Big Shack and Dubai Chocolate Shake\n2. Two channels to compare: \n   - In-Shack kiosk orders (DIGITAL_DIRECT channel)\n   - Third-party delivery channels (THIRD_PARTY_DELIVERY channel group - UberEats, DoorDash, GrubHub)\n3. \"Attachment rates\" - this typically means the percentage of orders that included these premium LTOs\n4. Filter to top 20 highest-volume locations (by transaction count)\n\nThis is a menu_lto question because it involves:\n- Specific LTO items (Big Shack, Dubai Chocolate Shake)\n- Item-level performance across channels\n- Performance by location\n\nI should use the menu_lto tool to query this data. I need to:\n1. Identify the top 20 highest-volume locations\n2. Calculate attachment rates for each LTO item by channel and location\n3. Compare kiosk vs third-party delivery\n\nThe metric would be: (orders containing the LTO / total orders in that channel at that location) * 100\n\nLet me call the menu_lto tool to get this information.\n"
